  "prompt": "What are the symptoms of chronic constipation?",
  "response": "Chronic constipation symptoms include:\n\n1. Infrequent bowel movements (less than three per week)\n\n2. Difficulty passing stool\n- Straining during bowel movements\n- Hard or lumpy stools\n- Feeling of incomplete evacuation\n\n3. Physical discomfort\n- Abdominal bloating\n- Stomach pain or cramping\n- Feeling of fullness or pressure in the rectum\n\n4. Additional signs\n- Rectal discomfort\n- Need to manually assist bowel movements\n- Hard, dry stools\n- Reduced appetite\n- Nausea\n\n5. Potential complications\n- Hemorrhoids\n- Anal fissures\n- Rectal bleeding\n- Fecal impaction\n\n6. Associated symptoms\n- Fatigue\n- Weight changes\n- Reduced overall well-being\n\nIf symptoms persist for several weeks or are accompanied by severe pain or bleeding, it's recommended to consult a healthcare professional for proper diagnosis and treatment.\n\nRisk factors can include low fiber diet, dehydration, lack of physical activity, certain medications, and underlying medical conditions.",
